<article class="post-entry"> 
  <header class="entry-header">
    <h2 class="entry-hint-parent">Publishing an OPML Blogroll With Hugo
    </h2>
  </header>
  <div class="entry-content">
    <p>Hugo is the static site generating content management system that I use to publish this website. It works really well, and has some deep functionality that I’m not even touching. For instance, it can parse data files while generating the site - including JSON and XML - and can use the content of those files to display information on web pages.
I was going to follow some recipes that I found online, but they involved converting the OPML file into JSON to be read by Hugo....</p>
  </div>
  <footer class="entry-footer"><span title='2024-04-01 19:02:32 -0600 MDT'>April 1, 2024</span>&nbsp;·&nbsp;4 min</footer>
  <a class="entry-link" aria-label="post link to Publishing an OPML Blogroll With Hugo" href="https://darcynorman.net/2024/04/01/publishing-an-opml-blogroll-with-hugo/"></a>
